			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Dragon Necropolis Encounter #2<a name="66956"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 14 04 7:13 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Note that I did this before the DN patch, so not sure if any has changed since.  There are quite a few mobs popped when you zone in.  They are all over pased Jaled Dar, so run to setup spot invis, no illusions.  Hug north wall once past JD's room, don't agro any of the script mobs.  
<br />

<br />
Hsagra's Relics will be spawned, but this is just an NPC on the ground, that I didn't interact with.  There will be Vasthon standing on the angled platform, you can ignore him untill everything else is dead.
<br />

<br />
There are 7 liches, 4 of them skeleton models, 3 human models.  Each Lich has a unique name.  Each lich also has minions.  This is part that was weird for me.  The first time I tried this, and failed, each Lich had 2 minions.  The next week I tried again, but 3 of the 4 liches had only one minion.  This maybe the bug that was fixed in DN.  In any case, the minions of the skeleton liches are fuly mezzable, so you will have at most 8 of these.  The minions of the huan liches are not mezzable, so these must be off-tanked or kited.  Kiting will require less of the raid dedicated to off-tanking, but is more risky, due to both agro and leashing issues.
<br />

<br />
Do not try to kill the minions, since they die when their lich master dies. As such, designate a Main Assist for the raid, who will call for assists on the human liches first, then skelly liches.  The liches do not attack until they get to about 80 health if I remember right.  If you took too many deaths up to this point, levae one skelly lich up and undamaged with a chanter or bard keeping the two remaining minions locked.  Rez fast, since this event has a timer.  I never hit the timer myself, but others have reported it, so go quick.
<br />

<br />
Once the last skelly lich dies, Vaston becomes attackable.  He has a poison dot he AE's, but it didnt seem to do much damage relative to my max hp.  Once Vasthon dead, Dracoliche pops form Hsagra's Relics.  AE rampage with AE Dot.  All healers should have MGBs up for heals, as well as lots of group healing.  One group in my raid tried curing it, but it was more time and mana cost to cure than to just heal.
<br />

<br />
Let your DPS go all out, this is a fight very much like Trak used to be; win fast or not at all.  If you need any tips on this Step, let me know.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=954899">Kanarian</a>, Bard of Saryrn<br>
Composer of The War Council</span></td>
